summary.snippet: "Great service, delicious steak and Greek salad!!👌good place to eat!!"
"Breakfast all day, burgers, sandwiches, salads and some deep fried items."
"Great staff every time I visit, and high quality "homemade" feel to the food."

most_relevant.description: The waffle was at first undercooked. We alludes it to the waitress, and she immediately fixed it by serving us a perfectly prepared new one. All else is just as good as traditional American breakfast should be. It was a wonderful dining experience!
Visited this place for breakfast. The food was really good and the staff was very friendly. Great place for a quick and easy breakfast.

My wife and I visited our son at UofM, we visited the church he is attending and took him here to breakfast afterwards.  The food was quite good, and the service was excellent.  We will definitely be back.
Great food, atmosphere, and service! Highly recommended breakfast/brunch spot on Ann Arbor's Westside.

Friendly atmosphere, great service. What I thought was a clean place. My vegetarian omelet tasted like a never cleaned greasy grill. Dug the feta out and left the nasty egg. Disappointing, it really did have fresh spinach, unfortunately it could not be tasted as the nasty meat grease overpowered the omelet's subtle flavors.  It was distusting, a waste of $12.50. Sorry village kitchen.

A great small local Diner in Ann Arbor. Wasn't too busy on a Saturday morning around 8:30am with most seats available ordered take out and food was quick and delicious. It was $28 after two omelets and tax which seemed a tad pricey but it was the convenience for me.

Awesome little gem in West Ann Arbor, really gives a good picture of Ann Arbor and has awesome miruls on the walls of iconic places in AA. The food here is portioned generously and all at a fair price. The staff here are super accommodating and great! Would definitely recommend this place for travels or locals!
I went here and boy it was amazing. Great food. Great atmosphere. The service was excellent if this didn't have five stars I would give it more
